Determine how many five-digit numbers (base 10) meet the following criteria: 
(i) none of its digits are zero; 
(ii) it is a perfect square;
(iii) the first two digits form a two-digit square number;
(iv) the sum of the next two digits (treated as two separate digits) is a single-digit square;
(v) the entire number is divisible by 7.
$\text{(A)} \ 0 \quad  \text{(B)} \ 1 \quad  \text{(C)} \ 2 \quad  \text{(D)} \ 3 \quad  \text{(E)} \ 4$

Which digit of $.23456$ when changed to $8$, results in the largest number?
